name: Shrimp Kisses with Feta Cheese
author: molldoll
summary: You can never go wrong with shrimp and bacon, but add a little feta and jalapeno and you will be getting kisses from everybody!
ingredients: 3 large jalapeno peppers, seeded and cut into slivers
10 slices thick sliced bacon, cut in half
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-low heat, and lightly oil the grate
Use a sharp paring knife to cut down the backs of the shrimp nearly all the way through, so you can spread apart the two halves
Open up the shrimp and lay them out onto your work surface
Spoon some crumbled feta cheese onto each shrimp, then top with slivers of jalapeno pepper
Close up the shrimp and wrap each with a strip of bacon; secure with a toothpick
Cook on the preheated grill until the bacon has begun to crisp and the shrimp is no longer translucent in the center, 10 to 15 minutes
